dfischer.proxysniffer

Class HttpRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.proxysniffer.HttpRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    dfischer.proxysniffer.HttpRequestInterface

    public class HttpRequest
extends java.lang.Object
implements dfischer.proxysniffer.HttpRequestInterface
    Contains all recorded data of a HTTP request.
    See Also:
    HttpResponse, ProxyDataRecord

      • HttpRequest

        public HttpRequest(java.lang.String absoluteURL,
           java.util.Vector<java.lang.String> requestHeaderVector,
           byte[] requestContent,
           long requestStartDate,
           long socketOpenTime,
           long requestTransmitTime)
        Constructs a new instance - used to import HTTP request data from external tools. Note the HTTP request must be in "normal" format (but not in "proxy format").
        Parameters:
        absoluteURL - absolute URL, for example "https://www.proxy-sniffer.com/index.html"
        requestHeaderVector - HTTP request header. The vector must contain at least the first HTTP header field.
        requestContent - HTTP request content, can be null if no request content is available
        requestStartDate - HTTP request start date, elapsed milliseconds since January 1. 1970, GMT.
        socketOpenTime - time in milliseconds used to open the network connection to the web server, can be -1 if no such time is available
        requestTransmitTime - time in milliseconds used to transmit the HTTP request to the web server, can be 0 if no such time is available

      • HttpRequest

        public HttpRequest(java.io.PushbackInputStream bin,
           dfischer.proxysniffer.ProxySSLServerData sslServerData,
           java.util.Vector externalReceiveLog,
           java.lang.String webSocketHost,
           int webSocketPort)
            throws java.io.IOException
        Constructor used when http request is being read in websocket connecten header request, here host:port is passed to the header from previous 'CONNECT example.com:80 HTTP/1.1'
        Parameters:
        bin - Input stream from Browser
        sslServerData - data for a proxy SSL tunnel server.
        externalReceiveLog - log vector
        webSocketHost - host from 'CONNECT example.com:80 HTTP/1.1'
        webSocketPort - port from 'CONNECT example.com:80 HTTP/1.1'
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Exception in case of socket failure.
        Since:
        V5.4-K

      • decompressContent

        public void decompressContent()
        Decompress the request content (only) if it is in compressed data format. Already decompressed request content will not be changed.
        Note 1: the method getCompressedContentUncompressed() will return a value of true if the request content was decompressed by this method.
        Note 2: the request header field "Content-Encoding" is NOT DELETED if the request content data are decompressed.
        Note 3: the request header field "Content-Length" is updated to the length of the decompressed data if the request content data are decompressed.
        See Also:
        getCompressedContentUncompressed()
